  "plan": "## ComparativeMarkerSelection GenePattern Module — Implementation Plan\n\n### 1. Overview\nComparativeMarkerSelection is a GenePattern module that Identify differentially expressed genes that can discriminate between distinct classes of samples.\n\n### 2. Parameters\nThe module exposes 14 parameters:\n- Required: input.file, cls.file, test.direction, test.statistic, number.of.permutations, log.transformed.data, complete, balanced, random.seed, smooth.p.values, output.filename\n- Optional: confounding.variable.cls.file, min.std, phenotype.test\n\n### 3. Command Line\n```\njava <java_flags> -Dlibdir\\=<libdir> -cp /opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/colt.jar\\:/opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/commons-math-1.2.jar\\:/opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/gp-modules.jar\\:/opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/Jama-1.0.2.jar\\:/opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/jsci-core.jar\\:/opt/genepattern/modules/ComparativeMarkerSelection/trove.jar org.broadinstitute.marker.MarkerSelection <input.file> <cls.file> <number.of.permutations> <test.direction> <output.filename> <balanced> <complete> no <test.statistic> <random.seed> false <smooth.p.values> -l<log.transformed.data> -m<min.std> -c<confounding.variable.cls.file> -p<phenotype.test>\n```\n\n### 4. Docker Image\nDocker image: genepattern/comparativemarkerselection\\:v11\n\n### 5. Validation Strategy\n- Validate all required parameters are provided\n- Validate file formats match expected extensions\n- Check parameter value ranges where applicable\n\n### 6. Implementation Roadmap\nPhase 1: Wrapper script implementation\nPhase 2: Docker container setup\nPhase 3: Parameter validation and error handling\nPhase 4: Testing and documentation",
